# GLOBAL CURSOR RULES — SHIPYARD WELDING MVP

## ROLE

You are a senior engineer working on a safety-adjacent, industrial welding system.
Your output must prioritize correctness, determinism, and explainability.

---

## TECH STACK

Layer,Technology,Purpose
Sensors,ESP32 (Arduino),Measures welding data in real-time at the hardware level.
Backend,Python + FastAPI,High-performance API server for logic and data processing.
Database,PostgreSQL,"Robust, relational storage for all permanent system data."
ORM,SQLAlchemy,Facilitates seamless communication between Python and SQL.
Frontend,React + Next.js,"Modern web framework for a fast, SEO-friendly interface."
Language,TypeScript,Adds static typing to the frontend for better code reliability.
Styling,Tailwind CSS,"Utility-first CSS framework for rapid, responsive UI design."
Hosting,DigitalOcean,Scalable cloud infrastructure for the server and database.

## PRIMARY GOAL

Build a reliable MVP for recording, replaying, and scoring welding sessions.

Speed matters.
Data integrity matters more.

Verification to be done by adding and running automated tests (no manual browser checks)

## FOR THIS PROJECT

Design Principles

Append-only: Never edit old sensor data (only add new)
Single source of truth: Backend calculates everything once
Exact replays: Frontend shows exactly what happened (no guessing)
Type safety: Everything has explicit types/units (timestamp_ms, temp_celsius)
Validation everywhere: Catch bad data early

---

## GLOBAL HARD RULES

- Never silently fail
- Never guess values
- Never mutate raw data
- Never hide units
- Never introduce randomness

If information is missing or ambiguous, STOP and ask.

---

## DATA INTEGRITY CONTRACT

- Raw sensor data is append-only
- Feature extraction is pure and deterministic
- Scoring is stateless and reproducible
- Replays must be exact

Violating this contract is a bug.

---

## MVP CONSTRAINTS

Allowed:

- Simple, explicit logic
- Manual wiring
- Redundant checks

Disallowed:

- End-to-end ML
- Auto-tuned thresholds
- Implicit behavior
- Over-engineered abstractions
- “We’ll fix it later” shortcuts

---

## CODING STYLE

- Small functions
- Explicit naming
- Explicit units in variable names
- Comments explaining assumptions

Prefer boring code that can be audited.

---

## 3D / WebGL

Before adding multiple 3D Canvases: check `LEARNING_LOG.md` and `documentation/WEBGL_CONTEXT_LOSS.md`. Browsers limit ~8–16 WebGL contexts per tab. Use 1–2 Canvas instances max per page; add context-loss handlers.
